<br>
so the best line of the movie has to be when bush is something like, &quot;...so i'm here with the haves, and the have mores.  some call you the nations elite, i call you my base...&quot; <br>
he also has other clips from various officials that are rather amusing.  it was interesting learning about bush's links to the bin laden family, though.  it turns out that he's been connected with them since the 70s or 80s (quite awhile, i forget i was a touch on the inebriated side).  they've actually invested tons of money into one of his former oil companies.  there's alot of interesting information that is totally skipped over by any news program i've ever seen (except the bbc).<br>
<br>
really, as far as i'm concerned the best parts of the movie don't even have him in them.  this was much better than his two prior videos i think.  he realies less on interviews, narratives, and filming himself, rather, focusing on samples from other journalists.  he does still appear in and narrate the movies, however, i found the most convincing arguments in the presentation of speeches and events documented.<br>
<br>
all of you people who are super right wing conservative should just watch this movie to get an idea of why people are against the bush administration.  wait untill its at the dollar theater or what have you, but at least give it a chance.  it did rather well here in conservative indiana -- which is saying quite a bit.<br>
<br>
