<br>
Further, my problems are less with authentic supply side theory which advocates both low taxes *and* fiscal responsibility, than with the politicially expedient partisan flavor of that theory.  Republicans use the parts of supply side theory convenient to them to justify their own long held dogmatic party plank of tax cuts to the wealthy.  <br>
<br>
David Stockman, the supply side hawk under Reagan admitted openly in his interview in the Atlantic that &quot;supply side that was always a Trojan horse to bring down the top [tax] rate...It's kind of hard to sell 'trickle down, so the supply-side formula was the only way to get a tax policy that was really 'trickle down.&quot;<br>
--The Atlantic Monthly, December 1981 <p>Bumraz, EQ Shadowknight<br>
